Boil a full #kettle.

Peel and grate the @garlic cloves{2} (or use a #garlic press{}).

Pour the boiled water into a large #saucepan{} with @salt{1/2%tsp} on high heat.

Stir the @macaroni{180%g} into the water and bring back to the boil. Cook until tender, ~{12%minutes}.

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of @oil{drizzle} in a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once hot, add the @diced British chicken breast{260%g} to the pan and season with @salt{} and @ground black pepper{}.

Fry until golden brown on the outside and cooked through, ~{8-10%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its packaging. It's cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Halfway through cooking, add the @British smoked bacon lardons{90%g} to the pan. Stir-fry for the remaining time, ~{4-5%minutes}, until golden.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw meat. Cook bacon thoroughly.

Once the chicken and bacon is cooked through, reduce the heat to medium and add the garlic, @tomato puree{30%g} and @Cajun spice mix{1%sachet} (add less if you'd prefer things milder). Stir-fry for ~{1%minute}.

Stir in the @chicken stock paste{10%g}, @creme fraiche{150%g}, @water{100%ml} and half the @grated hard Italian style cheese{20%g}. Bring to the boil.

Lower the heat and simmer until slightly thickened, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Meanwhile, once the macaroni is cooked, drain in a #colander{} and pop back into the pan.

Drizzle with oil and stir through to stop it sticking together.

Add the @baby spinach{40%g} to the chicken pan a handful at a time until wilted and piping hot, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Stir through the cooked macaroni. Taste and season with salt and pepper if needed. Add a splash of water if you feel it needs it.

Remove from the heat.

Share the Cajun style macaroni between your #serving bowls{}.

Sprinkle over the remaining cheese to finish.

Enjoy!